## Dynamic IDs for Collections

When rendering collections, include a unique identifier:

```erb
<!-- Rails ERB example -->
<% @articles.each do |article| %>
  <%= turbo_frame_tag dom_id(article) do %>
    <article id="<%= "article-#{article.id}-card" %>">
      <h2 id="<%= "article-#{article.id}-title" %>">
        <%= article.title %>
      </h2>
      <div id="<%= "article-#{article.id}-metadata" %>">
        <%= article.created_at %>
      </div>
      <div id="<%= "article-#{article.id}-actions" %>">
        <%= link_to "Edit", edit_article_path(article), 
            id: "article-#{article.id}-edit-link" %>
        <%= link_to "Delete", article_path(article), 
            id: "article-#{article.id}-delete-link",
            method: :delete %>
      </div>
    </article>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
```

**Pattern:** `[resource]-[id]-[element]-[type]`

